bulsi and his cabinet\nhave not yet submitted their resignations\nto King Hussain, despite their decision\non 31 March to do so in an effort to force\na showdown.\n\nThe cabinet apparently continues to hope\nthat it can through intimidation prevent the king from carrying\nout a series of political moves to arrest Jordan's leftist drift.\nThe cabinet also objects,\nto Hussain's opposition to its efforts to reorganize the government and the electoral machinery, and to \"his constant contacts with America without reference to the government.\"\n\nNabulsi and his cabinet appear to believe\nthat without representatives of the parties in the present cabinet,\nHussain could not form a government with sufficient popular support to maintain order. They are reportedly prepared to support their stand with the threat of calling out leftist mobs.. Nabulsi is reported to have appealed personally to Jordan's Communist Party \"to stand by and be ready to fight the king", "token_count": 162, "token_end_0based": 161, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "1 the situation in jordan comment on prime minister nabulsi and his cabinet have not yet submitted their resignations to king hussain despite their decision on 31 march to do so in an effort to force a showdown the cabinet apparently continues to hope that it can through intimidation prevent the king from carrying out a series of political moves to arrest jordan's leftist drift the cabinet also objects to hussain's opposition to its efforts to reorganize the government and the electoral machinery and to his constant contacts with america without reference to the government nabulsi and his cabinet appear to believe that without representatives of the parties in the present cabinet hussain could not form a government with sufficient popular support to maintain order they are reportedly prepared to support their stand with the threat of calling out leftist mobs nabulsi is reported to have appealed personally to jordan's communist party to stand by and be ready to fight the king", "unred_source_page": 4}
